MCSettings.Name: Dutch Revit Standards (NLRS) / AIK oktober 2022
MCSettings.Author: NLRS / AIK
MCSettings.Description: These checks are provided by the Dutch Revit Standards Foundation and can be used to validate a model's compliance with the Dutch Revit Standards (NLRS) document, version 3.0.1.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of loadable families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of loadable families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of system family types which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. System Panels are excluded from this check.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of system family types.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of detail component families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of detail component families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of Area Schemes (OST_AreaSchemes) which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. BuiltInCategory OST_Areas is undefinable by default and won't be checked.
Check.FailureMessage: For instance, schemes should be named "NLRS_00_AREA_gebruiksoppervlakte"

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of in-place families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of in-place families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of (both loadable and system) Structural Foundations which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS. Includes the check for Foundation Slabs and Wall Foundations.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of Structural Foundation families. Remark: a distinctive difference exists between sytem families (such as foundation slabs and wall foundations), and loadable structural foundations.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of Railings which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Separate check because there are 25+ BuiltInCategories available for railings and its subcategories.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of in-place families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of Stairs which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Separate check because there are 20+ BuiltInCategories available for stairs and its subcategories. Includes Cut Marks, Supports, Risers and Landings, where applicable.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of Stairs

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of profiles which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of profiles.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of Assemblies which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of in-place families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of different Insulation Types which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of in-place families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of annotation symbols which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS. The following symbols are checked: LevelHeads, ElevationMarks, SectionHeads, SpotElevationSymbols, CalloutHeads, GridHeads, ViewportLabels and View Reference Tags.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of annotation symbols.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of generic annotations which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of annotation symbols.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of View References which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Remark: a View Reference must be placed in the file before it can be checked.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of view references.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of tag families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of annotation symbol families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of symbol families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of symbol families.
There are non-compliant Title Blocks in this project

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of line patterns which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of fill (hatch) patterns which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check to determine if there are names of filled region components which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of filled region components and fill (hatch) patterns.

Check.Description: Lists all Line Styles in a Revit model.

Check to determine if there are names of Text Styles which are not compliant with positions 1 and 2 in the NLRS. Position 3 must be filled too and can contain any character up to a maximum of 246 characters.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of Text Styles.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of Dimension Styles which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Position 3 must be filled too and can contain any character up to a maximum of 246 characters.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant Dimension Styles.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of annotation symbols which are not compliant with positions 1 through 4 in the NLRS. The following symbols are checked: LevelHeads, ElevationMarks, SectionHeads, SpotElevationSymbols, CalloutHeads, GridHeads, ViewportLabels and View References.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of annotation symbols.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are view template name which are not compliant with positions 1 through 6 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant View Templates.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are Materials which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Position 3 must be filled too and can contain any character up to a maximum of 246 characters. The materials already existing in a clean Revit template are excluded from this check.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of materials.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are Appearance Assets which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Position 3 must be filled too and can contain any character up to a maximum of 246 characters.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of Appearance Assets found.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are Physical and/or Thermal Assets which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Position 3 must be filled too and can contain any character up to a maximum of 246 characters.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant items of Physical and/or Thermal Assets found.

Check.Description: Check to determine if the Assembly Code parameter is compliant with the (xx.xx) NL-SfB, table 1 classification system.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant Assembly Codes.

Check.Description: Lists all non built-in categories and sub-categories in a Revit model.
Reports the coordinates of the survey and project base points, elevation, and true north. Check if these are according to the Bim Execution Plan.
Reports the path of the current shared parameters file. Check if these are according tot the BIM Execution Plan.

Heading.Description: Checks that have been created but not placed in the structure yet.

Section.Title: Checks that have not been placed

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of Curtain Wall Panels not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Due to the standard built-in "System Panel" this check always returns a fail.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of curtain wall panels.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of tag families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of annotation symbol families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are names of tag families which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of annotation symbol families.

Check.Description: Check to determine if there are Materials which are not compliant with positions 1 through 3 in the NLRS. Position 3 must be filled too and can contain any character up to a maximum of 246 characters.
Check.FailureMessage: There are non-compliant names of materials.
